A true locals corner bar, one of the very few remaining in the city.  Good food, especially the crispy cracker pizza.  There's a reason it's been around as long as it's been.  If you're looking for a chill place and vibe where a friendly local will probably buy a round of drinks or shots, this is it.  You can play pool or darts without waiting hours or be scared of injuring anyone because it's too crowded.

Worst experience ever. Only customers getting service were at bar & they had all been there awhile. Bartender/waitress greeted us when we walked in, but took at least 10 minutes before she came to our table. Asked how long for a pizza & she said “20 minutes, fast.” I ordered a beer that was delivered warm & 50 minutes later we got our pizza & a Caesar salad we ordered along with pizza- both came out together & pizza cheese was burned & chicken on salad burned & dry. Waitress explained that several pizza carry outs had just come in before our order & that the oven is small - how long do customers wait when they’re busy, we were the only sit-down customers in the place? Very disappointed as their ratings do not speak the truth!
